body:
@ianlancetaylor is correct. cmd/9l/9.out.h has \r\n as line delimiters on windows. And cmd/dist uses \n to split the file in lines. So some consts end-up with \r inside of them. ...

Like I said above, we could fix cmd/dist (I think we should) and let users set core.autocrlf to whatever they like. Up to you.

Alex
